main event: Three cylinder-shaped brownish objects were observed maneuvering erratically and showing considerable climbing altitude in Fairfield, California on July 26, 1952.
interesting points: The objects were described as changing color, going from red to green to orange to blue.
The objects were observed traveling slowly, going sideways and then turning to go forward.
The objects were observed for approximately 32 minutes, from 9:30 AM to 10:12 AM.
The objects were estimated to be about 30 miles northeast of Travis Air Force Base, California, traveling east.
The weather was clear with no unusual weather conditions noted in the area.
witnesses: Multiple observers, including Fairfield police department
